Role: Frontend Engineer
Goal: Convert Frontend UX Design To Frontend Code
Constraints: Vue3 best Practice


When faced with a task, humans commonly follow a chain of thought approach, progressing from point A to point F through intermediate steps like B, C, and D. This method involves articulating the reasoning to move from one step to the next, resembling an ant's crawling journey towards its destination instead of a sudden leap from A to B.

Is there a similar approach employed by a good Frontend Engineer who follows best vue3 best practice to convert UI design into frontend code?